.TH "init.ee" "5" "2026-04-18"
.PP
.SH NAME
.PP
init.\&ee - configuration file for the ee text editor
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
The \fB.\&init.\&ee\fR file is used to set default modes and key bindings for the \fBee\fR(1)
text editor.\& The editor searches for this file in the following locations, in
order of precedence:
.PP
1.\& \fB/usr/share/misc/init.\&ee\fR
2.\& \fB$HOME/.\&init.\&ee\fR
3.\& \fB.\&init.\&ee\fR in the current working directory
.PP
The file consists of one command per line.\& Commands are case-insensitive.\&
.PP
.SH COMMANDS
.PP
\fBCASE\fR, \fBNOCASE\fR
.RS 4
Enable or disable case-sensitive searching.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBEXPAND\fR, \fBNOEXPAND\fR
.RS 4
Enable or disable the expansion of tabs to spaces.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBINFO\fR, \fBNOINFO\fR
.RS 4
Enable or disable the information window at the top of the screen.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBMARGINS\fR, \fBNOMARGINS\fR
.RS 4
Enable or disable the observation of margins.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBAUTOFORMAT\fR, \fBNOAUTOFORMAT\fR
.RS 4
Enable or disable automatic paragraph formatting.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBEIGHTBIT\fR, \fBNOEIGHTBIT\fR
.RS 4
Enable or disable support for eight-bit characters.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBHIGHLIGHT\fR, \fBNOHIGHLIGHT\fR
.RS 4
Enable or disable border and menu highlighting.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBEMACS\fR, \fBNOEMACS\fR
.RS 4
Enable or disable Emacs-style control key bindings.\&
.PP
.RE
\fB16BIT\fR, \fBNO16BIT\fR
.RS 4
Enable or disable support for 16-bit characters (e.\&g.\&, Big-5).\&
.PP
.RE
\fBRIGHTMARGIN\fR \fB\fRnumber\fB\fR
.RS 4
Set the right margin to the specified \fB\fRnumber\fB\fR.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBPRINTCOMMAND\fR \fB\fRcommand\fB\fR
.RS 4
Set the command used for printing (default is \fBlpr\fR).\&
.PP
.RE
\fBECHO\fR \fB\fRstring\fB\fR
.RS 4
Print \fB\fRstring\fB\fR to the message line during initialization.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBBIND\fR \fB\fRkey\fB\fR \fB\fRcommand\fB\fR
.RS 4
Bind a base control key.\& \fB\fRkey\fB\fR can be a control character (e.\&g.\&, \fB\(haA\fR),
a modified key (e.\&g.\&, \fBM-a\fR for Alt-a, \fBW-x\fR for Super-x, \fBC-c\fR for Ctrl-c,
\fBS-u\fR for Shift-u), or a literal code (e.\&g.\&, \fBcode:513\fR).\&
.PP
.RE
\fBGBIND\fR \fB\fRkey\fB\fR \fB\fRcommand\fB\fR
.RS 4
Bind a GOLD mode key (triggered after \fB\(haG\fR).\& Supports the same formats
as \fBBIND\fR.\&
.PP
.RE
\fBEBIND\fR \fB\fRkey\fB\fR \fB\fRcommand\fB\fR
.RS 4
Bind a key in Emacs mode.\& Supports the same formats as \fBBIND\fR.\&
.PP
.RE
.SH BINDABLE COMMANDS
.PP
The following internal commands can be used with \fBBIND\fR, \fBGBIND\fR, and \fBEBIND\fR:
.PP
\fBright\fR, \fBleft\fR, \fBup\fR, \fBdown\fR, \fBbol\fR, \fBeol\fR, \fBnext_page\fR, \fBprev_page\fR,
\fBtop_of_txt\fR, \fBbottom_of_txt\fR, \fBdel_char\fR, \fBdel_word\fR, \fBdel_line\fR, \fBund_char\fR,
\fBund_word\fR, \fBund_line\fR, \fBcopy\fR, \fBcut\fR, \fBpaste\fR, \fBappend\fR, \fBmark\fR, \fBsearch\fR,
\fBsearch_reverse\fR, \fBsearch_prompt\fR, \fBreplace_prompt\fR, \fBcommand_prompt\fR,
\fBgold_toggle\fR, \fBredraw\fR, \fBhelp\fR, \fBmenu\fR, \fBformat\fR, \fBadv_word\fR, \fBprev_word\fR,
\fBnewline\fR, \fBbackspace\fR.\&
.PP
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
.nf
.RS 4
INFO
NOCASE
RIGHTMARGIN 78
BIND ^A top_of_txt
BIND M-f next_page
BIND W-q menu
BIND code:262 bol  # Bind Home key if it sends code 262
GBIND ^X format
.fi
.RE
.PP
